commit.message:
Deprecate `RecordEntry.validate`

This function is no longer meant to be used, since there's a superior
alternative available.

Validate RECORD file using streams instead of reading in-memory

This ensures that the hashing logic within the codebase does not attempt
to read large files into memory, which can cause OOM issues.

Add `validate_stream` methods to `Record` and `Hash`

This ensures that the validation can be performed without loading a
file in-memory.

Fix the docstring of `copyfileobj_with_hashing`

This had the wrong ordering.

Add an empty `.git-blame-ignore-revs` file

This makes a global `blame.ignoreRevsFile` configuration behave cleanly.

Don't import other modules from `.utils`

This ensures that we don't rely on other modules to implement core
functionality.

Migrate `noxfile.py` to utilize pip install directly

It is reasonable to expect `pip` to support editable and non-editable
installs with flit.

Decouple `test_utils` from `test_records`

These two files should not import from each other.
Complete type annotations and strictify mypy (#173)
